lly SC'd crafted gear. It makes an almost unimaginable difference and I did point out that knowing whether someone's stats and skills were maxed was important. You'll only max these in SC'd gear. Of course damage is also affected by additional factors such as RR and RAs but the first step is getting that good gear.<br>
<br>
I also think that you have to make full use of your styles by using the best ones available, which for the most part doesn't mean using Ammy Slash and pick the weapon best suited to your purpose and play style. I'm frequently dismayed at seeing Mercs who have never learned to use positionals and reactionals and then make remarks such as the one I quoted, which is why I mainly responded to that.<br>
<br>
Edit: Next important is investing in good RAs. A Merc who's mezzed doesn't do much damage. Determination 4tehwin!<br>
<br>
