<br>
There are lots of times where my damage ends up being very low on casters. Typically, my mainhand is in the 200 range with offhand being in 60-100 range (I don't often get my offhand off on casters though, since i'm usually on support). This is with my 4.0 longsword.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I three shotted an elf caster a few days ago. Talking to other mercs, all being higher RR, say they are able to 3 shot casters almost reliably. Yet, there are still times where they do marginal damage to casters.<br>
<br>
There's a combination of things that causes it. Ablatives and PBT are what I consider the reasons why i'm unable to hurt casters effectivly half the time. On my server, no mid/hib group runs emain without one or the other, or both. Since Albion PBT is in the earth theurg class, we hardly ever get it (the line consists of only BTs).<br>
<br>
It's not all that fun, but that's how it is. The times where i'm able to three shot casters (only done once so far) is what keeps me playing. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
Darktendrils - 4x Necromancer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kawdor>Kawdor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(8/28/03 9:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mercs don't suck</span><hr size=1> Not disagreeing with you Rosimond, disagreeing with Fingoniel saying SC'ing isn't essential. Actually (thinking about it) not really disagreeing with Fingoniel either, no it is not essential, but you are doing yourself a disservice not having the best equipment available. And currently the best possible gear is player crafted and spellcrafted and then Alch'd.<br>
<br>
RA's make a big difference but to get those RA's you have to survive the battles you are in and nothing helps more than having your stats maxed from SC'd gear.<br>
<br>
Yes Ammy slash sucks compared to styles, it is only the best ANYTIME style, it is sooo very satisfying to hear the sound of a positional landing. <br>
<br>
Mercs don't suck, I love playing Kawdor, he's not perfect, like I'm not perfect but I can work around his deficiencies and still more than do my job in a group whether it is PvE or RvR.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#000000>(8/29/03 5:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=85>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: merc dmg</span><hr size=1> TatsumaruIII, I've thought this thread was dead a couple of times, but it keeps springing back to life. <br>
<br>
I'm not someone who looks at their hits a lot. As long as they end up dead at my feet, I figure I've done my job and don't worry much about it to much. And more often then not that's exactly where they end up. That's partly due to running with good CC. No I don't get those big hits that I got with an Armswoman but I don't miss and stand there for 5 more seconds either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I suppose SC'd gear isn't *essential* in that you can play and eventually be successful without it. But I've played Rosimond from day 1 in SC'd gear and comparing it to playing in drop, let me tell you the difference is almost unbelieveable. You probably can't afford it if you don't have a high level char to fund your Merc, but if there's any way you can possibly afford it, that's the ONLY way to go.<br>
<br>
One of my pet peeves is people who think that because Ammy Slash will land (and I do use it quite a bit on purple con mobs) then it's the best style to use in all situations. To play a Merc well you have to learn to use positionals and use them well. Is it always easy? Of course not and in a real lag fest it may be impossible. But it makes a big difference in a successful Merc and an unsuccessful Merc. <br>
